CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 25, 1957, pg. A17 reads: "Lovely Misses...who curtsied at the AKA Debutante Cotillion were Myra Eddins, Barbara Charles, Adrian Phillips, Roberta Durham, Frieda Maxine Brown and Alice Jean Weatherly."image of woman standing center, possibly Frieda Maxine Brown, not in negative, pasted in image published by Pittsburgh Courier.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five young women wearing light colored evening gowns, including Marva Jones wearing eyeglasses and Alice Jean Weatherly standing on right, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Alpha Kappa Alpha 1957 Cotillion
